<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-05-09T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-05-09T00:00:00-05:00" n="1555" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1555">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 819.00/393.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Minister</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Panama</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-05-09">
                                    <hi rend="italic">May 9, 1912</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Porras and Díaz both absent in the interior, but the leaders of both
                            parties have to-day affirmed to me over their signatures that Porras and
                            Díaz both desire American supervision of registration and election. This
                            I believe to be true. The written statements were signed for Porras by
                            Mendoza, Valdés and Chiari; for Díaz by President Arosemena. I recommend
                            our acquiescence, and believe the committee as described could devise
                            suitable measures in the manner indicated, as Governor Thatcher is on
                            leave. President Arosemena has asked me by a note just received to urge
                            my Government to accede to the request of the Government of Panama.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Dodge.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>